<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-234-292  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 234 292.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>The Seybold Report on Desktop Publishing  March 5 1990 v4 n7p46(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Seybold Publications Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Type 1, Type 3 format interchange facility: may support Nimbus-QFontographer hints. (Image Club Graphics' Evolutionfont-conversion utility program) (The Latest Word) (productannouncement)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Image Club Graphics Inc. (product introduction).andO;Product:   Evolution (Add-in/on software) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     FontsData ConversionUtility ProgramsProduct IntroductionDesktop Publishing.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Type 1, Type 3 format interchange facility Image Club Graphics announced thatit would shortly release a Macintosh utility program to convert Type 3 fontsinto type 1 fonts or vice versa.andP;  The program will also be able to convertType 1 or Type 2 fonts and characters into Adobe Illustrator files, where avariety of letterform-distortion effects could be done.andM;The utility, called Evolution, will be priced at $99.andM;Since Type 3 fonts do not contain hints, the resulting Type 1 fonts will nothave them, either.andP;  However, Image Club said that it has hopes for anautomatic conversion of the Nimbus-Q hints that Fontographer 3.0 inserts.andP;  Inaddition, it hopes to have a user-adjustable regularization(grid-constraining) function in the converter.andP;  This would provide anadjustable snap-to-grid effect on the character outlines, and should improverendering on screens and on 300-dpi laser printers.andM;The upshot would be to allow most of the Type 3 fonts from Cassady-Green,Image Club and other font designers to be used with Adobe type Manager andEmerald City's Type-Align.andP;  Conversely, it would allow Adobe Type 1 fonts(and those from Linotype, Monotype, Agfa Compugraphic, etc.) to be used inolder PostScript--clone printers by converting them to Type 3 format.andO;</TEXT></DOC>